NBA ALL-STAR 2019
February 16, 2019
Ben Simmons
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
 Q.  Why did you get into playing basketball?  
BEN SIMMONS: My father.  I think my dad was definitely the reason I got into playing the game, and I fell in love with that from them.   
 Q.  What does it mean to you to be able to give back?  
BEN SIMMONS: A lot.  Anytime you get an opportunity to represent your country, state, whatever it is, I think it's an amazing opportunity to take advantage of.   
 Q.  What's your mindset going into the game, and how do you feel about being an All Star?  
BEN SIMMONS: I think just looking forward to it.  Looking forward to the first experience for me to be an All-Star.  I think it's going to be a great opportunity.  Looking forward to it.  I'm competing against the best guys in the world.   
 Q.  How's your dad feel about it?  
BEN SIMMONS: He's really happy.  I put in a lot of work, spent a lot of time in the gym trying to get better.  So I know he's happy.   
 Q.  On the NBA's international growth:  
BEN SIMMONS: It's huge.  You can see now internationally the game's gotten a lot bigger.  The stage is a lot bigger.  Guys from overseas can easily come and play in the league.  It's gotten a lot bigger.   
 Q.  What's been your biggest basketball rivalry over the years?  
BEN SIMMONS: Rivalry?  I haven't had one.  I haven't had one of those matchups yet.   
 Q.  What about the first guy you went against that you wanted to go against?  
BEN SIMMONS: It's always Bron.  Competing against Bron is fun.   
 Q.  How would you describe Nikola Jokic?  
BEN SIMMONS: He's hard to guard.  Physically, he's a big guy.  He can score the ball, he can shoot outside the paint, he can pass the ball.  He can bring it up.  He can really do everything.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT